Ok, so, what do we all think of the new @lotuscars EMIRA?! Give me them opinions!

A £60k, 400bhp, V6 (for now) mid-engined sports car, and honestly it's bloody beautiful! It sounds sick as well!
-
-
I had the opportunity to spend my time at @fosgoodwood
With Lotus these last two days and seeing the reaction and interest to the Emira was MEGA! It's basically styled like the Evija as well which is a huge win in my mind!
-
-
I need one. I also need to modify one...😂
-
-
Massive thanks to the hospitality @lotuscars & @lotuspr

node.text:
Trying something super different from my usual style here for the next @meguiars post of the month, "The Popping 90s!". Using the Meguiars "Gold Class Line" as inspiration for this piece. 
-
-
This time, I went a bit more personal & drew on my love for what is easily my favourite 90's machine! The FD3S Mazda RX7. But with a bit of a difference....

Mazda never launched a Shootingbrake variant of the RX7, sure Greddy built a rear hatch, but I wanted to imagine something a bit more OEM. So i went about creating some 90's inspired Brochure adverts using my shooting brake concept, trying to make them look as if they belonged!
-
-
This was honestly SO MUCH FUN TO DO! To use one of my dream cars and try design something with it that didn't exist in a format I haven't really explored before. All this is 3D, a super simple setup but super effective I think also! Thanks Meguiars for allowing me to explore this concept! ❤
-
-

It's been a good 4 months or so since I had the time to do some personal work and this was an idea I've had for ages now & just couldn't shake. I really really wanted to slam a Zonda Cinque, keep it real clean & just enjoy the simplicity of it. The @rotiform LVS-Ms help immensely also 😂. Just super simple and most important, FUN!!
-
-
So happy with the outcome. Now that some of my bigger client projects are coming to an end (Can't wait to show you all!!), i will hopefully have time to continue my learnings and progression! ❤ Thanks again @colorsponge ❤ I made 20 renders of this 😁
-
